00:00:02.119 --> 00:00:03.319
we had the first couple of days,

00:00:03.319 --> 00:00:04.920
and praise the Lord for the rain out there.

00:00:04.920 --> 00:00:06.519
It's good to see the rain.

00:00:06.519 --> 00:00:08.279
We got a lot of rain in California this year.

00:00:08.279 --> 00:00:09.119
It ended our drought.

00:00:09.119 --> 00:00:11.680
We thank God for that because we were really

00:00:11.680 --> 00:00:13.000
in serious drought conditions.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:15.239
So we're glad that the Lord blessed us this past year

00:00:15.239 --> 00:00:18.000
and answered prayer, and we saw a lot of rain out there,

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:19.500
so we were glad for that.

00:00:19.500 --> 00:00:21.319
Well, just a quick introduction.

00:00:21.319 --> 00:00:22.280
I'm Paul Mershon.

00:00:22.280 --> 00:00:24.040
I'm from Mira Mesa Bible Baptist Church

00:00:24.040 --> 00:00:26.239
in the beautiful city of San Diego.

00:00:26.239 --> 00:00:28.280
In fact, our motto is America's Finest City.

00:00:28.280 --> 00:00:29.760
We agree with that.

00:00:30.520 --> 00:00:31.360
So we love our city.

00:00:31.360 --> 00:00:33.919
We live north of the city up in the foothills,

00:00:33.919 --> 00:00:36.439
almost 1,000 feet, and we love where we live.

00:00:36.439 --> 00:00:38.040
We're in an orange grove, a couple acres,

00:00:38.040 --> 00:00:40.520
and it's quiet up there, and we got the coyotes

00:00:40.520 --> 00:00:41.919
and rattlesnakes and the bobcats

00:00:41.919 --> 00:00:43.360
and all the rest of that run around up there,

00:00:43.360 --> 00:00:45.080
but we love it up there.

00:00:45.080 --> 00:00:46.639
It's a real blessing to live in that area

00:00:46.639 --> 00:00:49.119
of Southern California.

00:00:49.119 --> 00:00:51.680
My wife and I, Linda, we've been married 58 years now.

00:00:51.680 --> 00:00:53.799
We have one daughter, just one child,

00:00:53.799 --> 00:00:56.880
and she has five, and they're all adults, now all married.

00:00:56.880 --> 00:00:58.479
We have 14 great-grandchildren.

00:00:58.479 --> 00:01:00.319
Praise the Lord for that, amen?

00:01:00.319 --> 00:01:01.639
And you say, now, Brother Mershon,

00:01:01.639 --> 00:01:04.440
you don't look old enough to have 14 great-grandchildren.

00:01:04.440 --> 00:01:05.959
Thank you, I appreciate that.

00:01:05.959 --> 00:01:07.760
Praise the Lord.

00:01:07.760 --> 00:01:08.720
We got married young.

00:01:08.720 --> 00:01:11.000
I was 10 and she was eight.

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:14.720
And we did get married young,

00:01:14.720 --> 00:01:17.760
and we tend to do that in our family.

00:01:17.760 --> 00:01:20.080
Why, I don't know, but we do, and we're glad we did.

00:01:20.080 --> 00:01:22.800
So Linda and I have been partners in life and ministry

00:01:22.800 --> 00:01:24.959
all these years, and I thank God for my precious wife.

00:01:24.959 --> 00:01:26.360
She's a blessing to me.

00:01:26.360 --> 00:01:27.480
She travels everywhere with me.

00:01:27.480 --> 00:01:29.239
I don't take meetings unless she goes.

00:01:29.239 --> 00:01:30.319
She has to come with me,

00:01:30.319 --> 00:01:32.440
and I don't want to be without my wife,

00:01:32.440 --> 00:01:33.559
so I thank the Lord for her,

00:01:33.559 --> 00:01:35.360
and she's been a blessing all these years.

00:01:35.360 --> 00:01:37.639
She takes care of the finances.

00:01:37.639 --> 00:01:40.720
She takes care of scheduling my meetings, amen?

00:01:40.720 --> 00:01:42.400
She washes my clothes.

00:01:42.400 --> 00:01:44.120
She cooks my meals.

00:01:44.120 --> 00:01:45.040
Praise the Lord, amen?

00:01:45.040 --> 00:01:46.040
That's a good thing, eh?

00:01:46.040 --> 00:01:46.879
Aren't you glad?

00:01:46.879 --> 00:01:48.080
I mean, she does all that for me,

00:01:48.080 --> 00:01:50.239
and I just can't get, when we were pulling the RV,

00:01:50.239 --> 00:01:51.519
I couldn't get her to pull the RV.

00:01:51.519 --> 00:01:54.120
She wouldn't drive the truck, so I had to do all that,

00:01:54.120 --> 00:01:55.319
but I praise the Lord for her.

00:01:55.319 --> 00:01:57.040
We're from Miriam Mason Bible Baptist Church

00:01:57.599 --> 00:01:58.440
in San Diego.

00:01:58.440 --> 00:01:59.919
My pastor's Willie Dale.

00:01:59.919 --> 00:02:01.160
We're a Filipino church.

00:02:01.160 --> 00:02:02.519
You notice I'm not Filipino,

00:02:02.519 --> 00:02:05.480
but we have worked with Filipino people for years.

00:02:05.480 --> 00:02:07.800
I spent a lot of time in the Philippine Islands

00:02:07.800 --> 00:02:09.520
and fell in love with the Filipino people

00:02:09.520 --> 00:02:11.199
and the Philippines itself.

00:02:11.199 --> 00:02:13.199
If God allowed me to be a missionary down there,

00:02:13.199 --> 00:02:14.440
I would have been there years ago,

00:02:14.440 --> 00:02:16.199
but God's never given me permission

00:02:16.199 --> 00:02:18.479
to do mission work in the Philippines.

00:02:18.479 --> 00:02:20.000
We've been back down there and preached

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:23.000
and been in several churches in the Philippines.

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:25.080
There's a major moving of God going on

00:02:25.080 --> 00:02:28.360
in the 7,043 islands of that great country.

00:02:28.360 --> 00:02:32.279
The population now is getting close to 100 million people.

00:02:32.279 --> 00:02:36.360
Now, that country is being evangelized in a great way,

00:02:36.360 --> 00:02:38.399
and we thank God for that.

00:02:38.399 --> 00:02:39.759
So the Filipino people now,

00:02:39.759 --> 00:02:41.240
there's a lot of independent Baptist churches

00:02:41.240 --> 00:02:42.600
that have been established in the country.

00:02:42.600 --> 00:02:45.440
They've got Bible colleges going on, Bible institutes,

00:02:45.440 --> 00:02:48.960
and they're planning mission works all over the world

00:02:48.960 --> 00:02:50.479
out of the Philippines.

00:02:50.479 --> 00:02:51.800
And they say in the next five years,

00:02:51.800 --> 00:02:54.199
they'll be the greatest missionary sending nation

00:02:54.240 --> 00:02:56.320
on the face of the earth.

00:02:56.320 --> 00:02:57.160
They have missionaries there.

00:02:57.160 --> 00:03:00.320
You can go anywhere in the world, you'll find Filipinos.

00:03:00.320 --> 00:03:01.800
My pastor was recently in the Middle East,

00:03:01.800 --> 00:03:04.320
and he was preaching in underground churches there

00:03:04.320 --> 00:03:08.520
in Dubai and Bahrain, Bahrain, and then was up in Italy.

00:03:08.520 --> 00:03:11.039
And he said, man, there's Filipino churches

00:03:11.039 --> 00:03:12.559
because there's a lot of Filipinos

00:03:12.559 --> 00:03:14.520
that are working in the Middle East.

00:03:14.520 --> 00:03:16.600
And they go in there and they plant churches.

00:03:16.600 --> 00:03:18.199
And so we're thankful for what they're doing.

00:03:18.199 --> 00:03:19.199
We love our pastor.

00:03:19.199 --> 00:03:20.960
We love our church family.

00:03:20.960 --> 00:03:22.080
He's getting ready to retire.

00:03:22.080 --> 00:03:23.399
We have a new young man that's come in.

00:03:23.399 --> 00:03:25.119
We think he's gonna be taking the church.

00:03:25.119 --> 00:03:25.960
We're glad for that

00:03:25.960 --> 00:03:28.119
because he's just a really good young fellow.

00:03:28.119 --> 00:03:29.960
So we're excited about what God is doing.

00:03:29.960 --> 00:03:32.240
So we're glad to be with you, amen.

00:03:32.240 --> 00:03:33.399
And we appreciate you.

00:03:33.399 --> 00:03:34.759
I want you to know right from the very beginning,

00:03:34.759 --> 00:03:36.639
we love you and we care about you

00:03:36.639 --> 00:03:38.440
and we care about your pastor and his family.

00:03:38.440 --> 00:03:40.119
As he said, I was his pastor at one time.

00:03:40.119 --> 00:03:42.080
He just had brother Derrick Thomas here.

00:03:42.080 --> 00:03:43.320
I was his pastor also.

00:03:43.320 --> 00:03:47.160
One time I was ascending pastor when he went to Lithuania.

00:03:47.160 --> 00:03:48.679
Now, of course, he's working in Ukraine

00:03:48.679 --> 00:03:51.119
with Slavic Baptist missions there,

00:03:51.119 --> 00:03:52.240
Slavic Baptist Institute.

00:03:52.240 --> 00:03:54.160
