Now, I'm not going to preach out of this chapter.

00:04:04.039 --> 00:04:06.520
I'm gonna go back to the New Testament,

00:04:06.520 --> 00:04:08.639
but I want you to look at Jeremiah chapter 33

00:04:08.639 --> 00:04:10.639
as we begin this revival meeting.

00:04:12.800 --> 00:04:16.359
This may be one of the most important statements I make

00:04:16.359 --> 00:04:17.519
at the beginning of this meeting.

00:04:17.519 --> 00:04:19.079
I'm gonna be sharing a lot of different things

00:04:19.079 --> 00:04:19.920
with you through the week,

00:04:19.920 --> 00:04:21.640
but this is one of the most important statements

00:04:22.040 --> 00:04:25.079
I can possibly make as we begin this meeting.

00:04:25.079 --> 00:04:26.640
I see this as an imperative,

00:04:26.640 --> 00:04:27.760
what I'm gonna share with you right now.

00:04:27.760 --> 00:04:30.760
This is a revival meeting imperative.

00:04:30.760 --> 00:04:32.399
In Jeremiah chapter 33,

00:04:32.399 --> 00:04:34.559
a familiar portion of scripture says this,

00:04:34.559 --> 00:04:36.320
beginning in verse one,

00:04:36.320 --> 00:04:38.320
"'Moreover, the word of the Lord came unto Jeremiah

00:04:38.320 --> 00:04:40.119
the second time while he was yet shut up

00:04:40.119 --> 00:04:42.480
in the court of the prison, saying,

00:04:42.480 --> 00:04:44.640
thus saith the Lord, the maker thereof,

00:04:44.640 --> 00:04:47.239
the Lord that formed it to establish it,

00:04:47.239 --> 00:04:49.359
the Lord is his name.'"

00:04:49.399 --> 00:04:50.799
Now look at verse 33, it says,

00:04:50.799 --> 00:04:54.000
"'Call,' it says, "'call unto me,

00:04:55.279 --> 00:04:57.799
