00:04:57.799 --> 00:04:59.000
Now listen, when God answers,

00:04:59.000 --> 00:05:01.359
He may say yes, no, or wait.

00:05:03.799 --> 00:05:06.320
Did you ever think about that when you pray?

00:05:06.320 --> 00:05:09.119
Sometimes God will say yes and answer the prayer.

00:05:09.119 --> 00:05:13.200
Sometimes He'll say no, and sometimes He'll say wait.

00:05:13.200 --> 00:05:15.559
But I guarantee you, God's gonna answer prayer

00:05:16.480 --> 00:05:18.239
one way or the other.

00:05:18.239 --> 00:05:20.799
And we sure wanna see God answer prayer this week.

00:05:21.760 --> 00:05:24.720
So He said, "'Call unto me, and I will,'

00:05:24.720 --> 00:05:26.000
that's a great promise of scripture,

00:05:26.000 --> 00:05:29.320
"'I will answer thee and show thee great and mighty works

00:05:29.320 --> 00:05:31.559
or mighty things which thou knowest not.'"

00:05:31.559 --> 00:05:33.000
Now the word there, call, in verse three,

00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:33.839
is an interesting word.

00:05:33.839 --> 00:05:35.399
It's a Hebrew word, kora, and it means this.

00:05:35.399 --> 00:05:37.640
It means to cry out, to cry for help,

00:05:37.640 --> 00:05:40.679
to utter a loud sound, or to plead.

00:05:42.040 --> 00:05:43.040
So God's literally saying here,

00:05:43.040 --> 00:05:44.440
I want you to plead with me.

00:05:46.160 --> 00:05:47.559
I want you to call out to me.

00:05:47.880 --> 00:05:48.720
I want you to cry out.

00:05:48.720 --> 00:05:52.239
I want you to cry out in a distinct and definite manner.

00:05:53.799 --> 00:05:55.200
I need to hear from you.

00:05:56.480 --> 00:05:59.600
And I guarantee you, you're gonna hear from me, amen?

00:05:59.600 --> 00:06:01.600
And notice He said, listen, He said,

00:06:01.600 --> 00:06:04.000
"'Once again, call unto me, and I will answer thee

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:05.600
"'and show thee great and mighty things.'"

00:06:05.600 --> 00:06:07.519
That word mighty there, if you were to consider

00:06:07.519 --> 00:06:10.320
what was synonymous with it, be the word supernatural.

00:06:11.399 --> 00:06:13.260
And supernatural things which thou knowest not.

00:06:13.260 --> 00:06:15.100
God does supernatural things.

00:06:16.100 --> 00:06:20.059
We serve a powerful God, would you agree?

00:06:21.059 --> 00:06:22.579
And I thank God for that.

00:06:22.579 --> 00:06:25.700
Now let me say this, God is only limited by our unbelief.

00:06:26.899 --> 00:06:29.739
The only thing that limits God's working is our unbelief.

00:06:31.619 --> 00:06:34.339
Now I'll tell you what, I'm believing God for revival.

00:06:35.899 --> 00:06:39.739
Now God can only send revival if we plead with Him for it.

00:06:39.739 --> 00:06:41.019
And what I say in Sunday school,

00:06:41.019 --> 00:06:42.739
we have to meet the requirements to have revival

00:06:42.739 --> 00:06:44.380
if my people which are called by my name

00:06:44.459 --> 00:06:46.540
will humble themselves and pray and seek my face

00:06:46.540 --> 00:06:48.459
and turn from their wicked ways.

00:06:48.459 --> 00:06:51.179
Those four prerequisites must be met by God's people.

00:06:51.179 --> 00:06:52.700
Leave any one of them out,

00:06:52.700 --> 00:06:54.459
and we're not going to see revival.

00:06:55.619 --> 00:06:57.059
So God puts it on us.

00:06:58.380 --> 00:07:00.459
God says, if you will, I will.

00:07:00.459 --> 00:07:02.779
You see that in Malachi chapter three,

00:07:02.779 --> 00:07:04.579
God said, if you will, I will.

00:07:05.579 --> 00:07:07.940
And then sometimes I think God says, you first.

00:07:09.079 --> 00:07:10.179
You go first.

00:07:11.339 --> 00:07:13.019
Now we don't respond to God that way,

00:07:13.019 --> 00:07:13.899
there's not much you can do.

00:07:14.500 --> 00:07:15.420
Now Lord, listen, I want to come before you

00:07:15.420 --> 00:07:16.500
and I want to humble myself.

00:07:16.500 --> 00:07:17.779
I want to come broken.

00:07:19.179 --> 00:07:20.980
Lord, I want to humble myself before you,

00:07:20.980 --> 00:07:22.899
I want to come broken.

00:07:22.899 --> 00:07:23.940
I don't want to hide anything,

00:07:23.940 --> 00:07:25.100
don't want to cover anything up,

00:07:25.100 --> 00:07:26.299
I don't want to hold anything back.

00:07:26.299 --> 00:07:28.600
I want to come and I just want to come broken.

00:07:29.500 --> 00:07:31.260
I want to humble myself before you.

00:07:32.140 --> 00:07:34.380
I'm going to seek you in prayer.

00:07:34.380 --> 00:07:36.140
I'm going to bow myself before you.

00:07:36.140 --> 00:07:38.660
And oh, and I'm going to turn from my wicked ways.

00:07:39.700 --> 00:07:42.179
It's an amazing thing that God says that to his own people,

00:07:42.260 --> 00:07:44.380
the children of Israel, and he says the same thing to us.

00:07:44.380 --> 00:07:45.739
He said, and sometimes people say,

00:07:45.739 --> 00:07:49.420
that doesn't go down well with me, but it's what God said.

00:07:49.420 --> 00:07:51.579
I'm not going to change the word of God.

00:07:51.579 --> 00:07:52.859
God wrote it, I quoted, he said,

00:07:52.859 --> 00:07:55.140
you need to turn from your wicked ways.

00:07:56.540 --> 00:07:59.179
Anything that's in violation of God's word is wicked.

00:08:00.779 --> 00:08:03.140
Any sin that we commit against God is wicked.

00:08:05.619 --> 00:08:07.179
Amen.

00:08:07.179 --> 00:08:09.619
And God says, you know what, you know, folks,

00:08:09.619 --> 00:08:11.339
you just need to realize the importance

00:08:11.339 --> 00:08:12.660
of meeting these prerequisites.

00:08:12.660 --> 00:08:14.779
